Package: sddr
Title: Spatial Distribution Dynamics
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Muhammad", "Farooqi",
           email = "mqfarooqi@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4918-9791"))
Description: A tidy toolkit for the analysis of distribution dynamics: how a
    cross-sectional distribution of values evolves over time. Provides
    discrete-time Markov transition estimation, ergodic (steady-state)
    analysis, and - across later releases - spatial Markov chains, rank
    mobility, continuous stochastic kernels and modern inference. Methods
    build on the distribution-dynamics literature (Quah (1993)
    <doi:10.1016/0014-2921(93)90031-3>) and are designed around long-format
    'id'/'time'/'value' data rather than transition matrices, so that panel
    data and (in later releases) 'sf' objects flow through unchanged.
